==English==
[[Image:Black scorpion.jpg|thumb|A Black Scorpion]]
===Etymology===
From Old (and modern) French ''[[#French|scorpion]]'', from Latin ''[[scorpio]]'', ultimately from Greek ''[[σκόρπιος]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈskɔ:pɪən/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any of various [[arachnids]] of the order Scorpiones, related to the [[spiders]], characterised by two large front pincers and a curved tail with a poisonous sting in the end.

